The 2019 MyBroadband Cloud Conference will be hosted on 6 June 2019 at Gallagher Estate in Midrand, Gauteng. It is the premier cloud event in South Africa and the meeting place for the country’s IT and cloud community. This year delegates can look forward to excellent speakers from all the major cloud and hosting players, including Liquid Telecom, Microsoft, and Amazon Web Services. South Africa’s top cloud companies, hosting and data centre players, and cloud communications providers will also exhibit their products and interact with IT decision makers. Liquid Telecom, a premier cloud and ICT provider in Africa, has joined the conference as the lead sponsor. Other prominent companies which will exhibit at the event include Connection Telecom, VMWare, Fortinet, Cipherwave, Westcon, Redstor, and Elingo. Registrations for the 2019 MyBroadband Cloud Conference are now open, with a big discount on early-bird tickets. To register or find out more, visit: 2019 Cloud Conference Website.